                    <section class="entry">
	                	<h1 style="text-align: left;">い Adjective Vocabulary (And How To Identify Them)</h1>
<h4 style="text-align: left;">“There are no ordinary moments.” <span style="color: #888888;">- Dan Millman</span></h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Before you take a look at the vocab, let&#8217;s learn how to identify い adjectives. There&#8217;s a hint in their name (like な adjectives), so this should be pretty simple. Let&#8217;s take a look at a sampling of い adjectives. See if you can figure out why they&#8217;re called that.</p>
<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;">おいしい　(tasty)<br />
いそがしい　(busy)<br />
あたらしい　(new)<br />
ちかい　(near)<br />
おおきい　(big)</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">If you guessed &#8220;they all have an い on the end&#8221; then you are right! Now, the tricky part is that there are some な adjectives that <em>also</em> have an い on the end (きらい and きれい, to name a few). Unfortunately, you&#8217;ll have to memorize these as exceptions if you don&#8217;t want to be confused by them. Just make sure you know your な adjective vocab list, and you should do just fine.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">So, it&#8217;s time for you to start learning the い adjective list. I&#8217;d recommend learning around 30% of these if you can, before moving on, since it&#8217;ll help you focus on your grammar (rather than trying to remember words). Then, import the i-adj deck to your TextFugu Vocab deck on Anki.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="woo-sc-ilink"><a class="info" href="../../../downloads/anki/vocab/i-adj.zip" style="background: url( http://tfugu.github.io/img/anki.png) no-repeat left 40%;">い Adjectives List</a></span> on Anki</p>
<p>There&#8217;s a lot more い adjectives than there were な adjectives, but all of these will be extremely useful to you. They are very common words, and words you&#8217;ll be able to <em>use</em> right away or in the near future.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Word</th>
<th>かな</th>
<th>Meaning</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
