<p style="text-align: left;">Along with this I&#8217;ve made a PDF reference sheet you can use. Make sure you don&#8217;t let it be your crutch, though. Learn the words, and only use this sheet to review / practice your words, if possible!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="woo-sc-ilink"><a class="download" href="../../../downloads/worksheets/i-adj-vocab.pdf">い Adjective Vocab List</a></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">After going through part of these words, move on to the next page, where you&#8217;ll start seeing how い adjectives are used (as well as how they&#8217;re similar / different from the な adjectives you learned earlier).</p>
<div class="woo-sc-box tick   ">By finishing this page, you&#8217;ve learned some of the い adjective vocabulary &#8211; make sure you continue to study these!</div>
